{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489476","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489476"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:18:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:18:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"669"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"669","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/669"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.69,0.11,0.01,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"669"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105970"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"669","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/669"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"669"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88445"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"191"},{"type":"tags","id":"351"},{"type":"tags","id":"502"},{"type":"tags","id":"1307"},{"type":"tags","id":"3505"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1393"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2077"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17235"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38881"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105970","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/105970"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 48-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic for assessment of obesity. He has a medical history of hypertension, gastro-oesophageal reflux disease and type 2 diabetes mellitus. His medications include atorvastatin, ramipril, esomeprazole and metformin. Six months ago he had a left knee arthroplasty. Despite dietary advice and lifestyle modifications over two years, he is unable to get his BMI below 35 kg/m2. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. He is counselled regarding possible bariatric surgery.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following surgical procedures would be most appropriate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Sleeve gastrectomy","Roux-en-Y gastric bypass","Laparoscopic gastric band","Biliopancreatic diversion with duodenal switch","Intragastric balloon"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ECurrent guidelines recommend considering bariatric surgery for patients with BMI \u0026gt;35 kg/m2, or BMI \u0026gt;30 kg/m2 with obesity-related conditions such as type 2 diabetes, hypertension, or gastro-oesophageal reflux disease. This patient meets these criteria and has multiple comorbidities that could improve with bariatric surgery. Worldwide this has changed, with medicare indications also changing - a recent draft by the Australian Government Department of Health and Aged Care also reflects this update.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERoux-en-Y gastric bypass\u003C/strong\u003E is most appropriate here given his pre-existing gastro-oesophageal reflux disease. It combines restriction (small gastric pouch) with malabsorption (intestinal bypass). Expected weight loss after 2 years is approximately 70%. It also provides excellent resolution of reflux symptoms and significant improvements in glycaemic control.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESleeve gastrectomy\u003C/strong\u003E involves removing the greater curvature of the stomach to create a tubular stomach. While technically simpler than bypass, it can worsen reflux symptoms due to creating a high-pressure cavity. Given this patient\u0027s pre-existing reflux, sleeve gastrectomy would not be optimal.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELaparoscopic gastric band\u003C/strong\u003E is a purely restrictive procedure that has fallen out of favour due to high rates of long-term complications and band erosion. It achieves less weight loss than either bypass or sleeve procedures and often requires revision surgery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBiliopancreatic diversion with duodenal switch\u003C/strong\u003E combines sleeve gastrectomy with extensive intestinal bypass. While it achieves excellent weight loss, it has high rates of nutritional complications including malnutrition, anaemia, and vitamin deficiencies. It is generally reserved for super-obesity (BMI \u0026gt;50 kg/m2).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntragastric balloon\u003C/strong\u003E is a temporary intervention typically used as a bridge to more definitive surgery. The balloon is removed or passes spontaneously after several months, with most patients regaining weight unless they proceed to definitive bariatric surgery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe choice of bariatric procedure should consider patient factors including BMI, comorbidities, and patient preferences after thorough counselling about risks and benefits. This patient\u0027s reflux and diabetes make Roux-en-Y gastric bypass the optimal choice.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Roux-en-Y gastric bypass provides effective and sustained results for weight loss and management of type 2 diabetes.","Gastric bypass is preferred over sleeve gastrectomy in patients with pre-existing gastro-oesophageal reflux disease.","Current guidelines recommend considering bariatric surgery for BMI \u003E35 kg/m2 or \u003E30 kg/m2 with obesity-related conditions."],"references":["Kermansaravi, M., Chiappetta, S., Parmar, C. et al. Current recommendations for procedure selection in class I and II obesity developed by an expert modified Delphi consensus. Sci Rep 2024;14:3445. Available at: https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-024-54141-6#citeas","Nelson DW, Blair KS, Martin MJ. Analysis of obesity-related outcomes and bariatric failure rates with the duodenal switch vs gastric bypass for morbid obesity. Arch Surg. 2012;147(9):847-54. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/22987179/","Viscido G, Gorodner V, Signorini F, Navarro L, Obeide L, Moser F. Laparoscopic Sleeve Gastrectomy: Endoscopic Findings and Gastroesophageal Reflux Symptoms at 18-Month Follow-Up. J Laparoendosc Adv Surg Tech A. 2018;28(1):71-7. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29227187/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88445"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"669"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88445","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/88445"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-15T15:49:59+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-15T15:50:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"669"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"105970"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"dat